%20to%20trust%20that%20all%20these%20places%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20go%20and%20download%20these%20images%20from%2C%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20give%20you%20good%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20reason%20chatbots%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-is-like-many-other-ai-models-rife-with-bias-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erife%20with%20biases%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20flat-out%20provide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-may-provide-false-answers-to-medical-questions-study-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincorrect%20answers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20internet%20is%20full%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-scam-spam-hacking-ruining-internet-chatgpt-privacy-misinformation-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emisinformation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETram%C3%A8r%20and%20a%20team%20of%20AI%20researchers%20then%20posed%20the%20question%20in%20a%20paper%20published%20in%20February%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2302.10149%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EarXiv%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20research%20paper%20platform%20hosted%20by%20Cornell%20University%3A%20Could%20someone%20deliberately%20%26quot%3Bpoison%26quot%3B%20the%20data%20an%20AI%20model%20is%20trained%20on%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20that%20with%20some%20spare%20cash%20and%20enough%20technical%20know-how%2C%20even%20a%20%26quot%3Blow-resourced%20attacker%26quot%3B%20can%20tamper%20with%20a%20relatively%20small%20amount%20of%20data%20that's%20invasive%20enough%20to%20cause%20a%20large%20language%20model%20to%20churn%20out%20incorrect%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDead%20domains%20and%20Wikipedia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETram%C3%A8r%20and%20his%20colleagues%20looked%20at%20two%20kinds%20of%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20hackers%20could%20poison%20the%20data%20is%20by%20purchasing%20expired%20domains%2C%20which%20can%20cost%20as%20little%20as%20%2410%20a%20year%20for%20each%20URL%2C%20and%20then%20putting%20any%20kind%20of%20information%20they%20want%20on%20the%20websites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20%2460%2C%20Tram%C3%A8r's%20paper%20said%2C%20an%20attacker%20could%20purchase%20domains%20and%20effectively%20control%20and%20poison%20at%20least%20.01%25%20of%20a%20dataset.%20That%20amounts%20to%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20an%20attacker's%20perspective%2C%20this%20is%20great%20because%20it%20gives%20them%20a%20lot%20of%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Tram%C3%A8r%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Tram%C3%A8r%2C%20the%20team%20tested%20this%20attack%20by%20looking%20at%20datasets%20other%20researchers%20rely%20on%20to%20train%20real%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarge-models-can-create-new-smaller-ai-tools-scientists-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20purchasing%20expired%20domains%20within%20those%20datasets.%20The%20team%20then%20monitored%20how%20often%20researchers%20downloaded%20from%20the%20datasets%20that%20contained%20domains%20Tram%C3%A8r%20and%20his%20colleagues%20owned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20domains%20under%20his%20control%2C%20Tram%C3%A8r%20could%20tell%20researchers%20trying%20to%20download%20the%20data%20that%20a%20particular%20image%20was%20%26quot%3Bno%20longer%20available.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20he%20could%20have%20given%20them%20whatever%20he%20wanted%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20single%20attacker%20could%20control%20a%20large%20enough%20fraction%20of%20the%20data%20that%20is%20used%20to%20train%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20machine%20learning%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20Tramer%20said%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Binfluence%20how%20this%20model%20behaves%20in%20some%20sort%20of%20targeted%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20attack%20Tram%C3%A8r%20and%20his%20colleagues%20looked%20into%20involved%20poisoning%20data%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-wikipedia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWikipedia.%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20site%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20prime%20component%20of%20the%20training%20sets%26quot%3B%20for%20language%20models%2C%20Tram%C3%A8r%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20internet's%20standards%2C%20it's%20a%20very%20high-quality%20source%20of%20text%20and%20sources%20of%20facts%20about%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it's%20the%20reason%20researchers%20give%20%26quot%3Bextra%20weight%26quot%3B%20to%20data%20from%20Wikipedia%20when%20training%20language%20models%20even%20though%20the%20website%20makes%20up%20a%20small%20part%20of%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETram%C3%A8r's%20team%20outlined%20a%20fairly%20unsophisticated%20attack%20involving%20carefully%20timed%20Wikipedia%20page%20edits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWikipedia%20doesn't%20allow%20researchers%20to%20scrape%20from%20their%20website%20but%20instead%20provides%20%26quot%3Bsnapshots%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20pages%20that%20they%20can%20download%2C%20Tram%C3%A8r%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20snapshots%20are%20taken%20at%20regular%20and%20predictable%20intervals%20that%20are%20advertised%20on%20Wikipedia's%20website%2C%20according%20to%20Tram%C3%A8r.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20a%20malicious%20actor%20could%20time%20edits%20to%20Wikipedia%20just%20before%20a%20moderator%20can%20revert%20the%20changes%20and%20before%20the%20website%20takes%20snapshots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20if%20I%20want%20to%20go%20and%20put%20some%20junk%20on%20the%20Wikipedia%20page%20of%20say%2C%20Business%20Insider%2C%20I'm%20just%20going%20to%20do%20a%20little%20math%2C%20estimate%20that%20this%20particular%20page%20is%20going%20to%20be%20saved%20tomorrow%20at%203%3A15%20p.m.%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Btomorrow%20at%203%3A14%20p.m.%20I'm%20going%20to%20add%20junk%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETram%C3%A8r%20told%20BI%20that%20his%20team%20didn't%20perform%20real-time%20edits%20but%20instead%20calculated%20how%20effective%20an%20attacker%20could%20be.%20Their%20%26quot%3Bvery%20conservative%26quot%3B%20estimate%20was%20that%20at%20least%205%25%20of%20edits%20made%20by%20an%20attacker%20would%20make%20it%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20practice%2C%20it%20will%20likely%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20than%205%25%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20some%20sense%2C%20for%20these%20poisoning%20attacks%2C%20it%20doesn't%20really%20matter.%20You%20usually%20don't%20need%20all%20that%20much%20bad%20data%20to%20get%20one%20of%20these%20models%20to%20suddenly%20have%20some%20new%20unmated%20behavior.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETram%C3%A8r%20said%20that%20his%20team%20presented%20the%20findings%20to%20Wikipedia%20and%20provided%20suggestions%20for%20safeguards%2C%20including%20randomizing%20the%20time%20the%20website%20takes%20snapshots%20of%20its%20web%20pages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Wikipedia%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20during%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20future%20of%20data%20poisoning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETram%C3%A8r%20told%20BI%20that%20if%20the%20attacks%20are%20limited%20to%20chatbots%2C%20then%20data%20poisoning%20wouldn't%20be%20an%20immediate%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20more%20anxious%20about%20a%20future%20where%20AI%20tools%20start%20to%20interact%20more%20with%20%26quot%3Bexternal%20systems%26quot%3B%20that%20will%20allow%20users%20to%2C%20say%2C%20instruct%20a%20ChatGPT-like%20model%20to%20browse%20the%20web%2C%20read%20your%20emails%2C%20access%20your%20calendar%2C%20or%20book%20a%20dinner%20reservation%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20many%20startups%20are%20already%20working%20on%20these%20types%20of%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20security%20perspective%2C%20these%20things%20are%20a%20complete%20nightmare%2C%26quot%3B%20Tram%C3%A8r%20said%2C%20because%20if%20any%20part%20of%20the%20system%20is%20hijacked%2C%20an%20attacker%20could%20theoretically%20command%20the%20AI%20model%20to%20search%20for%20someone's%20email%20or%20find%20a%20credit%20card%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETramer%20also%20adds%20that%20data%20poisoning%20isn't%20even%20necessary%20at%20the%20moment%20due%20to%20the%20existing%20flaws%20of%20AI%20models.%20Often%2C%20exposing%20the%20pitfalls%20of%20these%20tools%20is%20almost%20as%20simple%20as%20asking%20the%20models%20to%20%26quot%3Bmisbehave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20moment%2C%20the%20models%20we%20have%2C%20in%20a%20way%2C%20are%20brittle%20enough%20that%20you%20don't%20even%20need%20poisoning%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-poisoning-ai-chatbot-chatgpt-large-language-models-florain-tramer-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711248733000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ff805a16bde8d4ead18faf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-poisoning-ai-chatbot-chatgpt-large-language-models-florain-tramer-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20as%20little%20as%20%2460%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Blow-resourced%20attacker%26quot%3B%20could%20tamper%20with%20the%20data%20AI%20models%20are%20trained%20on%2C%20a%20researcher%20told%20Business%20Insider.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-poisoning-ai-chatbot-chatgpt-large-language-models-florain-tramer-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22National%20day%20of%20mourning%20in%20Russia%20after%20concert%20hall%20massacre%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711248598000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F