one%20during%20its%20next%20upgrade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20according%20to%20BofA's%20research%2C%20only%2055%25%20of%20Samsung%20users%2C%2043%25%20of%20Huawei%20users%2C%20and%2033%25%20of%20Xiaomi%20users%20said%20the%20same.%20This%20is%20corroborated%20by%202021%20data%20from%20research%20firm%20Consumer%20Intelligence%20Research%20Partners%2C%20which%20found%20that%20Apple%20had%20maintained%20a%20loyalty%20rate%20of%20more%20than%2090%25%20in%20the%20prior%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20argue%20that%20this%20isn't%20just%20because%20the%20company%20has%20been%20churning%20out%20great%20products.%20%26quot%3BMuch%20of%20it%20is%20due%20to%20the%20restrictive%20ecosystem%20that%20Apple%20has%20created%20around%20its%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20Andy%20Liu%2C%20a%20former%20student%20at%20Simon%20Fraser%20University%2C%20argued%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.lib.sfu.ca%2Findex.php%2Fslc-uwc%2Farticle%2Fview%2F3843%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20ecosystem%20means%20that%20the%20costs%20of%20switching%20over%20to%20other%20operating%20systems%20are%20too%20high%20for%20most%20users%2C%20and%20prevent%20them%20from%20accessing%20content%2C%20like%20music%20or%20apps%2C%20that%20are%20exclusive%20to%20Apple%2C%20Liu%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMessaging%20apps%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20Apple%2C%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20be%20the%20black%20sheep%20that%20responds%20to%20all%20their%20iPhone-using%20friends%20with%20a%20green%20bubble.%20The%20suit%20argues%20that%20Apple%20makes%20third-party%20messaging%20apps%20on%20the%20iPhone%20%26quot%3Bworse%26quot%3B%20than%20Apple%20messages.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20%26quot%3BApple%20is%20knowingly%20and%20deliberately%20degrading%20quality%2C%20privacy%2C%20and%20security%20for%20its%20users%20and%20others%20who%20do%20not%20have%20iPhones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESmartwatches%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20has%20left%20wearable%20enthusiasts%20in%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20conundrum.%20The%20company%20says%20its%20popular%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-apple-watch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20Watches%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%20work%20when%20paired%20with%20iPhones%2C%20and%20it%20won't%20build%20a%20version%20for%20Androids%20due%20to%20technical%20limitations.%20And%20if%20you're%20an%20iPhone%20user%20who%20wants%20to%20wear%20a%20Google%20Pixel%20Watch%20or%20Samsung%20Galaxy%20Watch%20%E2%80%94%20good%20luck.%20Apple%20doesn't%20plan%20to%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-android-smartwatches%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompeting%20watches%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20with%20iPhones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOJ%20argues%20that%20Apple%20limits%20smartwatch%20options%20for%20consumers%20by%20denying%20them%20%26quot%3Baccess%20to%20high%20performing%20smartwatches%20with%20preferred%20styling%2C%20better%20user%20interfaces%20and%20services%2C%20or%20better%20batteries%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20harms%20other%20smartwatch%20companies%20by%20%26quot%3Bdecreasing%20their%20ability%20to%20innovate%20and%20sell%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDigital%20Wallets%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20becoming%20more%20common%20for%20iPhone%20users%20to%20pay%20for%20items%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-pay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20Pay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company's%20digital%20wallet%20system.%20But%20Apple%20has%20blocked%20other%20developers%20from%20creating%20digital%20wallets%20on%20the%20iPhone%20with%20the%20same%20%26quot%3Btap-to-pay%20functionality%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20suit.%20Additionally%2C%20Apple%20also%20charges%20banks%20a%200.15%25%20fee%20on%20any%20transaction%20made%20through%20Apple%20Pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20argues%20that%20Apple%20essentially%20%26quot%3Bmaintains%20complete%20control%20over%20how%20users%20make%20tap-to-pay%20payments%20with%20their%20iPhone%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdeprives%20users%20of%20the%20benefits%20and%20innovations%20of%20third-party%20wallets.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-apple-is-a-monopoly-antitrust-lawsuit-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711220725000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fda2c74af076d3cf92b871%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-apple-is-a-monopoly-antitrust-lawsuit-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Is%20Apple%20a%20monopoly%3F%20Here%20are%20some%20of%20the%20ways%20the%20Justice%20Department%20says%20it%20is.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40insider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-apple-is-a-monopoly-antitrust-lawsuit-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20party%20entrepreneurs%20bought%20'Beer%20Can%20Island'%20in%20Florida's%20Tampa%20Bay%20for%20%2463%2C000.%20They're%20now%20selling%20it%20for%20%2414%20million.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223964%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Palm%20trees%20at%20Clearwater%20beach%2C%20Tampa%2C%20Florida%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ff01173f923f7dab00950e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPalm%20trees%20at%20Clearwater%20beach%2C%20Tampa%2C%20Florida%3Cp%3EIxefra%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E'Beer%20Can%20Island'%20in%20Florida's%20Tampa%20Bay%20has%20been%20listed%20for%20sale%20at%20%2414.2%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFour%20friends%20purchased%20the%20island%20for%20%2463%2C000%20in%202017%2C%C2%A0The%20Times%20of%20London%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20faced%20challenges%20convincing%20locals%20to%20get%20on%20board%20with%20their%20business%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20party%20venue%20with%20a%20difference%20in%20Florida's%20Tampa%20Bay%20is%20up%20for%20sale%20for%20%2414.2%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPine%20Key%20is%20an%20island%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Tampa%20Bay%2C%20%3Cspan%3Ecreated%20by%20a%20state%20dredging%20project%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20It%20stretches%20some%2069%20acres%2C%20though%20only%20nine%20of%20these%20are%20above%20water%2C%20and%20boasts%20photogenic%20white%20beaches%20and%20surrounding%20blue%20waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20commonly%20known%20as%20'Beer%20Can%20Island'%20for%20the%20beer%20cans%20left%20behind%20by%20boaters%20but%20it%20has%20been%20transformed%20into%20one%20of%20Florida's%20party%20hot%20spots%20in%20the%20last%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20purchased%20by%20four%20entrepreneurial%20friends%20in%202017%20for%20%2463%2C650.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussell%20Loomis%2C%2046%2C%20who%20was%20one%20of%20the%20visionary%20quartet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Ffriends-cash-in-beer-can-island-party-plans-go-flat-g9wjr2smm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20The%20Times%20of%20London%3A%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BWe've%20worked%20our%20tails%20off%20for%20the%20last%20six%20years%20on%20this%20project%2C%20and%20we're%20just%20ready%20to%20pass%20the%20torch%20to%20the%20next%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20his%20LinkedIn%20profile%2C%20Loomis%20has%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Frussell-loomis-ba8b9247%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a%20business%20background%20in%20tech%20apps%20and%20running%20a%20debt%20relief%20company%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%202017%2C%20he%20built%20a%20floating%20tiki%20bar%20with%20friends%20from%20258%20plastic%20barrels.%20Finding%20a%20parking%20spot%20for%20their%20floating%20watering%20hole%20drew%20them%20to%20Pine%20Key.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20an%20extremely%20fun%20time%2C%20but%20it's%20come%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20challenges.%20We%20didn't%20know%20when%20we%20bought%20it%20what%20we%20were%20getting%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20purchased%20the%20island%2C%20which%20already%20had%20a%20reputation%20as%20an%20unofficial%20party%20spot%20for%20locals%2C%20it%20lacked%20facilities%20or%20utilities%2C%20and%20its%20owners%20seemed%20quite%20glad%20to%20be%20rid%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20years%20since%2C%20after%20hauling%20in%20food%20and%20alcohol%20supplies%2C%20fixing%20up%20toilets%2C%20picnic%20tables%2C%20and%20a%20120ft%20inflatable%20slide%2C%20the%20once%20defunct%20island%20has%20become%20a%20hub%20for%20boaters%20seeking%20to%20let%20their%20hair%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRunning%20an%20island%20is%20different%20to%20running%20a%20regular%20business.%20There's%20a%20whole%20new%20learning%20curve%2C%26quot%3B%20Loomis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20run%20a%20bar%20on%20the%20mainland%2C%20a%20truck%20shows%20up%20with%20all%20the%20inventory%2C%20and%20they%20come%20in%20and%20stock%20the%20shelves%3B%20with%20the%20island%2C%20you%20physically%20go%20shopping%2C%20load%20it%20into%20vans%2C%20off%20the%20vans%20into%20a%20boat%2C%20off%20the%20boat%20onto%20wherever%20it's%20going%20on%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20logistics%20are%20the%20most%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Loomis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENonetheless%2C%20Loomis%2C%20Cole%20Weaver%2C%20James%20Wester%2C%20and%20John%20Gadd%2C%20having%20invested%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fox13news.com%2Fnews%2Fbeer-can-island-tampa-goes-up-for-sale-closes-to-the-public-all-good-things-must-come-to-an-end%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%245%20million%20in%20the%20project%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20have%20turned%20the%20island%20into%20a%20hot%20spot%20for%20party-goers.%20They've%20even%20hosted%20weddings%20and%20music%20events%2C%20selling%20up%20to%203%2C000%20concert%20tickets%20a%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOthers%20weren't%20so%20keen%20on%20the%20friends'%20business%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20enjoyed%20the%20friends'%20decision%20to%20pimp%20out%20the%20island%2C%20some%20were%20less%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20core%20group%20of%20people%20thought%20it%20was%20their%20island%20and%20didn't%20understand%20that%20before%20we%20bought%20it%2C%20it%20was%20actually%20privately%20owned%2C%20and%20they%20were%20trespassers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20owner%20just%20didn't%20enforce%20it%2C%20so%20they%20felt%20entitled.%20We%20opened%20it%20up%20and%20created%20facilities%20and%20entertainment%2C%26quot%3B%20Loomis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20attempt%20to%20placate%20some%20locals%2C%20Weaver%20spent%20100%20days%20living%20on%20the%20island%2C%20building%20relationships%20with%20the%20boating%20community%20and%20reassuring%20them%20that%20they%20could%20still%20come%20to%20the%20island%20when%20they%20wished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeaver%2C%20%3Cspan%3Ean%20estate%20agent%20and%20architectural%20engineer%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20decided%20to%20keep%20most%20of%20the%20island%20open%20to%20anyone%20who%20wished%20to%20step%20ashore%20but%20sectioned%20off%20some%20of%20it%20for%20fee-paying%20%26quot%3Bmembers%20only.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocal%20authorities%20also%20kicked%20up%20a%20fuss%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20island%20ought%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20nature%20reserve%20rather%20than%20for%20parties.%20Manatees%20reside%20near%20to%20the%20island%2C%20seeking%20comfort%20in%20the%20warm%20waters%20during%20the%20winter.%20Weaver%2C%20though%2C%20believes%20the%20only%20wildlife%20that%20lives%20on%20the%20island%20are%20seagulls%20and%20a%20rat%20that%20pestered%20him%20during%2