i%20Airtel%20contributed%20the%20highest%20amount%20of%20Rs%20241%20crore%2C%20followed%20by%20Tata%20Steel%20(Rs%20175%20crore)%20and%20Larsen%20%26amp%3B%20Toubro%20(Rs%2085%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBharti%20Airtel%20emerged%20as%20the%20only%20Sensex%20company%20that%20consistently%20donated%20to%20political%20parties%20each%20year%2C%20in%20the%20past%20five%20financial%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20its%20annual%20reports%2C%20the%20company%20and%20its%20subsidiaries%20collectively%20donated%20Rs%20241%20crore%20to%20political%20parties%20between%20FY19%20and%20FY23%2C%20either%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20or%20contributions%20to%20electoral%20trusts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COther%20expenses%20include%20political%20contributions%20amounting%20to%20Rs%20300%20million%20(Rs%2030%20crore)%20and%20Rs%201%2C025%20million%20(Rs%20102.5%20crore)%20made%20under%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Act%20(Companies%20Act%2C%202013)%20during%20the%20year%20ended%20March%2031%2C%202023%20and%20March%2031%2C%202022%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Bharti%20Airtel%20in%20its%20annual%20report%20for%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20other%20index%20companies%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20list%20only%20sporadically%20reported%20expenditures%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20or%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20in%20their%20annual%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20L%26amp%3BT%20and%20Mahindra%20%26amp%3B%20Mahindra%20each%20reported%20making%20political%20donations%20twice%20in%20their%20annual%20reports%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20L%26amp%3BT%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2035%20crore%20and%20Rs%2050%20crore%20in%20FY19%20and%20FY20%20respectively%2C%20while%20M%26amp%3BM%20contributed%20Rs%201.02%20crore%20and%20Rs%2023%20crore%20to%20the%20New%20Democratic%20Electoral%20Trust%20in%20FY19%20and%20FY20%2C%20respectively.%20Neither%20company%20mentioned%20any%20other%20political%20donations%20or%20electoral%20bond%20purchases%20in%20subsequent%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20company%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20for%20Rs%2050%20crore%20and%20issued%20the%20same%20to%20political%20parties%20as%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20political%20contribution%2C%E2%80%9D%20L%26amp%3BT%20said%20in%20its%20annual%20report%20for%202019-20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETata%20Steel%2C%20which%20disclosed%20a%20donation%20of%20Rs%20175%20crore%20to%20an%20electoral%20trust%20in%20its%202018-19%20annual%20report%2C%20is%20not%20listed%20in%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20database%20of%20companies%20that%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20five%20other%20index%20companies%20reported%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20only%20once%20in%20the%20past%20five%20financial%20years%3A%20UltraTech%20Cement%20(Rs%2023%20crore%20in%20FY19)%2C%20Bajaj%20Finance%20(Rs%2020%20crore%20in%20FY20)%2C%20Maruti%20Suzuki%20(Rs%2020%20crore%20in%20FY23)%2C%20and%20Tech%20Mahindra%20(Rs%2015%20crore%20in%20FY20).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESun%20Pharmaceuticals%2C%20despite%20being%20recorded%20as%20purchasing%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2031.5%20crore%20since%20FY19%2C%20as%20per%20the%20Election%20Commission%20data%2C%20did%20not%20disclose%20this%20or%20any%20other%20political%20contributions%20in%20its%20annual%20reports%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20Instead%2C%20it%20only%20lists%20expenses%20on%20donations%20without%20detailing%20their%20breakdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711178927000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F14185439%2Fcoins-gebbaa9855_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fonly-eight-of-30-sensex-companies-disclosed-political-donations-in-past-five-fiscals-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Collectively%2C%20these%20companie