0Janata%20Dal.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Between%20April%2012%20and%20May%2010%2C%202019%2C%2013%20political%20parties%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%202%2C902.87%20crore%20in%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20of%20which%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20alone%20received%20Rs%202%2C719.32%20crore%20or%2093%25%20of%20the%20total%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20parties%20who%20received%20bonds%20included%20the%20Congress%20that%20received%20just%203.2%25%20or%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2095.29%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKolkata-based%20industrialist%20Mahendra%20Kumar%20Jalan%E2%80%99s%20firms%20and%20Hyderabad-based%20Megha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructure%20Limited%20(MEIL)%20were%20the%20top%20donors%20to%20political%20parties%20ahead%20of%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20data%20released%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20on%20March%2021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwho-were-the-top-buyers-of-electoral-bonds-paying%5C%22%3Ehas%20revealed.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20received%20Rs%2036.2%20crore%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20received%20Rs%2013.6%20crore%2C%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20received%20Rs%2010%20crore%2C%20and%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20received%20Rs%208.45%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20(SAD)%20received%20Rs%206.76%20crore.%20The%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%2C%20and%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20received%20Rs%202%20crore%20each.%20The%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%20got%20Rs%201.5%20crore%2C%20and%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20received%20Rs%201%20crore.%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20National%20Conference%20received%20Rs%2050%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F17272525%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%