ou%20watching.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Owen%20Gleiberman%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Freviews%2Fsleeping-dogs-review-russell-crowe-karen-gillan-1235949090%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Freviews%2Fsleeping-dogs-review-russell-crowe-karen-gillan-1235949090%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Freviews%2Fsleeping-dogs-review-russell-crowe-karen-gillan-1235949090%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Troubled%20Relationship%20with%20Law%2C%20Authority%2C%20and%20Justice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11082632%2FImage6.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20growing%20up%20in%20India%2C%20making%20sense%20of%20two%20distinct%20modes%20of%20public%20behaviour%20was%20often%20puzzling.%20In%20the%201980s%2C%201990s%2C%20and%20later%20on%20as%20well%2C%20light%20bulbs%20from%20the%20wagons%20of%20Indian%20railways%20were%20often%20found%20missing.%20Ironically%2C%20stealing%20and%20damaging%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epublic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20property%20was%20a%20form%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epublic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20protest%20or%20entertainment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20widespread%20public%20behaviour%2C%20which%20is%20still%20exhibited%2C%20is%20to%20invoke%20the%20fear%20of%2C%20or%20summon%2C%20the%20police.%20If%20a%20servant%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20stealing%20something%20or%20a%20worker%20is%20accused%20of%20defaulting%20on%20their%20work%2C%20the%20fear%20of%20the%20police%20is%20immediately%20invoked.%20In%20many%20other%20situations%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20degree%20of%20class%20and%20network-privilege%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ejugaad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20justice%20is%20initiated%20by%20finding%20connections%20in%20the%20police.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20another%20troubling%20and%20more%20institutionalised%20ritual%20of%20justice-deliverance%20that%20is%20practised%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98janta%20durbar%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3Eheld%20by%20political%20leaders%2C%20heads%20of%20states%2C%20and%20even%20bureaucrats%C2%A0to%20distribute%20on-the-spot%20justice.%20This%20is%20another%20variation%20of%20jugaad%20justice.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20law%E2%80%99s%20courts%20or%20normal%20course%20of%20administrative%20redressal%20are%20clearly%20not%20viewed%20as%20enough.%20The%20ruler%2C%20therefore%2C%20needs%20to%20organise%20a%20people%E2%80%99s%20court%2C%20that%20is%2C%20the%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%98janta%20durbar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98.%20Justice%20is%20served%20from%20within%20the%20apparatus%20of%20the%20law%20but%20by%20adopting%20a%20hyper-legal%20process%20of%20passing%20on-the-spot%20summary%20commands%20to%20the%20officials.%20This%20is%20a%20political%20form%20of%20legal%20mimicry%20which%2C%20while%20claiming%20to%20make%20justice%20accessible%2C%20reiterates%20the%20relationship%20of%20the%20ruler%20and%20the%20ruled%20in%20modern%20democracy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20do%20these%20actions%20by%20different%20stakeholders%20in%20providing%20justice%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20signify%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDamaging%20public%20property%20shows%20an%20alienated%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20people.%20The%20state%20ceases%20to%20remain%20an%20institution%20that%20ought%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20borne%20out%20of%20an%20equal%20stakeholding%20process%20between%20the%20government%20and%20its%20citizens.%20This%20can%20be%20read%20as%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20in%20forming%20a%20foundation%20of%20public%20and%20social%20morality.%20The%20law%E2%80%99s%20expectations%20towards%20public%20property%20are%20resisted%20and%20mocked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20second%20example%2C%20the%20state%2C%20through%20police%2C%20becomes%20an%20active%20and%20sought-after%20institution%20which%20acquires%20a%20close%2C%20and%20at%20times%2C%20intimate%2C%20kin-ly%20power%20over%20people.%20The%20punitive%20power%20of%20the%20same%20alienated%20state%20is%20readily%20used%20to%20seek%20justice%20by%20instilling%20fear%20in%20others.%20The%20police%20are%20both%20feared%20and%20favoured%20because%20it%20delivers%20summary%20justice.%20People%20tend%20to%20use%20the%20coercive%20legal%20power%20of%20the%20police%20for%20others%20even%20when%2C%20precisely%20for%20that%20same%20reason%2C%20they%20despise%20it%20being%20used%20upon%20themselves.%20The%20rule%20of%20law%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%20state-centric%2C%20neutral%20normative%20principle%20of%20justice%20%E2%80%93%20thus%20begins%20to%20appear%20in%20an%20uneasy%20relationship%20with%20the%20liking%20for%20summary%20justice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%20third%2C%20some%20may%20argue%20that%20it%20exemplifies%20persistence%20of%20culture%20through%20ancient%20and%20medieval%20times%20in%20which%20the%20king%20heard%20the%20complaints%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epraja%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20subjects%2C%20directly.%20The%20problem%20with%20this%20argument%20is%20that%20in%20monarchical%20dispensations%2C%20kings%20and%20queens%20personified%20justice%3B%20in%20modern%20times%2C%20the%20law%20is%20the%20king.%20And%20yet%2C%20patrimonial%20and%20monarchical%20forms%20of%20justice-deliverance%20persist%2C%20at%20least%20in%20its%20optic%20if%20not%20in%20content.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20this%20optic%20required%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20persistence%20is%20neither%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20survival%20of%20a%20cultural%20practice%20through%20time%20immemorial%20nor%20of%20anomalies%20of%20law%20and%20justice%20which%20would%20inevitably%20force%20a%20modern%20institution%20to%20remain%20dependent%20upon%20a%20premodern%20practice.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20we%20see%20in%20junta%20durbars%20is%20a%20well-crafted%20initiative%20to%20turn%20justice%20into%20a%20commodity%20of%20public%20consumption%3B%20a%20performance%20of%20ritual%20or%20spectacle%20in%20which%20the%20legislative%20openly%20directs%20and%20rebukes%20the%20executive%20under%20the%20claim%20of%20making%20justice%20publicly%20accessible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeen%20differently%2C%20what%20is%20being%20touted%20as%20personal%20involvement%20in%20promptly%20disbursing%20justice%20is%20actually%20a%20commentary%20on%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20procedural%20vitality%20of%20the%20law.%20For%2C%20had%20the%20law%20worked%20well%2C%20the%20need%20for%20simulation%20of%20divine%20intervention%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20head%20of%20state%20or%20political%20leaders%20would%20not%20have%20arisen%20in%20the%20modern%20state%20structure.%20And%20yet%2C%20in%20another%20sense%2C%20it%20reflects%20the%20perpetual%20dialectical%20character%20of%20the%20law%20in%20which%20justice%20ought%20to%20depend%20on%20or%20utilise%20the%20element%20of%20coercion%20which%20it%20tries%20to%20obliterate%20at%20the%20same%20time.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-unconstitutionality-of-bulldozer-justice%5C%22%3EThe%20Unconstitutionality%20of%20%E2%80%98Bulldozer%20Justice%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20these%20practices%20symbolise%20our%20troubled%20relationship%20with%20law%2C%20authority%2C%20and%20justice.%20We%20need%20the%20intervention%20of%20one%20to%20question%20the%20other%2C%20while%20seeking%20the%20third.%20Often%2C%20the%20retributive%20form%20of%20public-%2C%20mob-%2C%20jugaad-%2C%20or%20summary-justice%20triumphs%20over%20the%20processual%20nature%20of%20law%E2%80%99s%20justice%20through%20the%20mediation%20of%20a%20superior%20authority.%20They%20appear%20contradictory%20but%20they%20are%20not.%20Seen%20in%20a%20different%20manner%2C%20these%20are%20the%20two%20modalities%20of%20law%3A%20one%2C%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20which%20is%20procedural%20in%20nature%20and%20can%20take%20longer%20to%20materialise%2C%20and%20two%2C%20the%20rule%20of%20police%20which%20is%20instant%20and%20pervasive%20but%20delivers%20a%20summary%20form%20of%20justice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECan%20history%20of%20law%20and%20justice%20as%20it%20unfolded%20in%20India%20from%20the%20eighteenth%20century%2C%20when%20some%20of%20the%20basic%20foundations%20of%20the%20modern%20law%20were%20themselves%20being%20crafted%2C%20provide%20a%20clue%2C%20if%20not%20genesis%2C%20to%20some%20of%20the%20aspects%20of%20this%20troubled%20relationship%20between%20law%20and%20justice%3F%20The%20history%20of%20the%20emergence%20of%20the%20police%20in%20eighteenth%20century%20India%20can%20provide%20some%20explanation.%20It%20exposes%20the%20tussle%20between%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20police%20whose%20antecedents%20first%20take%20us%20to%20the%20eighteenth%20century%E2%80%99s%20foundational%20discussions%20on%20law%20and%20police.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERule%20of%20law%20versus%20the%20rule%20of%20police%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20from%20being%20of%20peripheral%20importance%2C%20law%20moved%20into%20the%20centre%20stage%20of%20peoples%E2%80%99%20lives.%20It%20became%20the%20principal%20source%20of%20life%E2%80%99s%20facts.%20It%20became%20the%20foremost%20mediating%20instrument%20in%20social%20and%20economic%20relationships%20related%20to%20work%2C%20employment%2C%20marriage%2C%20property%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERule%20of%20law%20is%20not%20a%20benign%20object%20of%20progress.%20It%20can%20be%20a%20political%20tool%20of%20social%20oppression%2C%20a%20bourgeois%20tool%20of%20class%20domination%2C%20and%20a%20tool%20for%20the%20underprivileged%20to%20fight%20for%20their%20liberties%20and%20rights.%20In%20general%2C%20it%20is%20a%20system%20through%20which%20power%20asymmetries%20in%20the%20society%20are%20both%20concretised%20and%20obscured%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaw%20can%20dominate%20in%20the%20name%20of%20equality%3B%20it%20can%20impose%20new%20social%20norms%20under%20the%20name%20of%20progress%20and%20development%3B%20and%20it%20can%20pervade%20into%20the%20most%20private%20of%20the%20private%20spheres%20in%20the%20name%20of%20security.%20However%2C%20the%20basic%20idea%20enshrined%20in%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20authority%20above%20the%20law.%20This%20is%20the%20general%20characteristic%20of%20law%E2%80%99s%20duality%3A%20it%20is%20an%20instrument%20of%20equality%20and%20justice%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20sort%20of%20fabric%20into%20which%20scripts%20of%20inequalities%20are%20stitched.%20Particularly%2C%20seen%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20criminal%20law%2C%20all%20modern%20laws%20including%20the%20colonial%20examples%2C%20simultaneously%20exhibit%20the%20dual%20feature%20of%20fairness%20and%20despotism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDistinct%20from%20this%20was%20the%20conceptual%20genealogy%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20police.%20In%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20the%20police%20were%20seen%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20establishing%20public%20well-being%2C%20industrious%20moral%20order%20and%20safety.%20Adam%20Smith%20regarded%20it%20as%20a%20means%20of%20satisfying%20the%20natural%20wants%20and%20demands%20of%20mankind.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20the%20German%20%3Ci%3EPolizei%3C%2Fi%3E%20had%20a%20similar%20meaning%3A%20it%20meant%20less%20the%20institutions%20for%20maintaining%20communal%20order%20than%20the%20condition%20for%20good%20order%20and%20prosperity%20in%20the%20community%20itself.%20It%20did%20not%20mean%20a%20uniformed%20force%20employed%20by%20the%20state%20to%20maintain%20law%20and%20order%20but%20a%20general%20system%20of%20government%20to%20regulate%20broad%20aspects%20of%20communal%20existence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20this%20idea%2C%20the%20police%20were%20not%20seen%20as%20a%20bureaucratic%20arm%20of%20the%20state.%20It%20rather%20borrowed%20the%20model%20of%20governance%20from%20the%20householder%E2%80%99s%20authority%20as%20applicable%20to%20the%20family.%20Thus%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20public%20safety%2C%20good%2C%20and%20happiness%20was%20premised%20upon%20discretionary%20and%20patriarchal%20order.%20In%20Blackstone%E2%80%99s%20views%2C%20the%20police%20would%20ensure%20good%20behaviour%20and%20manners%20of%20the%20individuals%20towards%20the%20state%20and%20fellow%20citizens%20similar%20to%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20family%20members%20towards%20the%20heads%20of%20the%20family.%20In%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98police%E2%80%99%20acquired%20the%20meaning%20akin%20to%20%E2%80%98science%20of%20government%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20meant%20to%20regulate%20public%20morals.%20But%20the%20sovereign%20was%20the%20paterfamilias.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20police%20were%20two%20distinct%20modes%20of%20government.%20The%20communitarian%20meaning%20of%20the%20police%20stood%20in%20opposition%20to%20law%20because%20ideologically%20law%20stood%20for%20the%20aggregate%20of%20individuals%20in%20which%20their%20personal%20and%20private%20rights%20were%20secured%20as%20long%20as%20they%20did%20not%20infringe%20upon%20others.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20objective%20of%20the%20law%20was%20not%20to%20secure%20a%20common%20good%20for%20all%20but%20to%20guarantee%20the%20rights%20of%20individuals.%20In%20reality%2C%20however%2C%20both%20modes%20constituted%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20making%20of%20the%20modern%20penal%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGradually%2C%20the%20language%20of%20law%20subsumed%20the%20model%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20police.%20In%20England%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20moderation%20in%20criminal%20law%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20prison%20as%20a%20primary%20form%20of%20punishment%2C%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20salaried%20professional%20police%20altered%20the%20notion%20of%20justice%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20Private%20prosecution%20and%20informal%20policing%20made%20way%20for%20public%20police%20system.%20There%20was%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20deepening%20of%20the%20police%20state%20over%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20largely%20accompanied%20by%20the%20separation%20of%20power.%20Police%20became%20a%20preventative%20force%2C%20devoid%20of%20judicial%20powers.%20The%20historical%20process%20was%20complicated%20and%20tardy%20but%20conceptually%2C%20law%20became%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20authority%20for%20justice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20theory%2C%20the%20police%20were%20entrusted%20with%20the%20prevention%20and%20detection%20of%20crime%2C%20but%20not%20with%20punishment.%20This%20is%20the%20modern%20meaning%20with%20which%20we%20identify%20the%20term%20police.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-in-india-requires-inspiration-from-the-tricolour-not-temple-dhwajas%5C%22%3EJustice%20in%20India%20Requires%20Inspiration%20from%20the%20Tricolour%2C%20Not%20Temple%20Dhwajas%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20question%20then%20is%3A%20what%20was%20the%20conceptual%20evolution%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20law%20and%20police%2C%20or%20between%20accountability%20in%20the%20law%20and%20discretion%20of%20the%20police%20power%2C%20in%20India%3F%20Was%20the%20summary%20power%20ever%20seen%20as%20an%20aberration%20to%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20or%20was%20it%20a%20necessary%20accompaniment%20of%20justice%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20emergence%20of%20police%20in%2018th%20century%20Calcutta%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201785%2C%20a%20new%20police%20Bill%20envisioning%20to%20grant%20the%20London%20police%20the%20power%20of%20arrest%20was%20rejected%20on%20grounds%20of%20defence%20of%20personal%20liberty%20and%20check%20on%20arbitrary%20power.%20The%20same%20year%2C%20in%20India%2C%20the%20justices%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Calcutta%20fined%20the%20police%20superintendent%2C%20Thomas%20Motte%2C%20and%20his%20deputy%2C%20Edward%20Maxwell%2C%20for%20exercising%20arbitrary%20power.%20This%20summary%20power%20existed%20in%20detaining%20people%20upon%20suspicion%2C%20inflicting%20punishment%20through%20various%20humiliating%20forms%20of%20flogging%2C%20public%20shaming%2C%20and%20imprisonment%20in%20a%20range%20of%20petty%20cases%20of%20crime%2C%20insolence%2C%20breach%20of%20contract%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20judgment%2C%20William%20Jones%20made%20a%20distinction%20between%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20apprehend%20offenders%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20and%20their%20power%20to%20deliver%20justice%20through%20punishment%20on%20the%20other.%20If%20the%20former%20is%20exercised%20in%20moderation%2C%20he%20noted%2C%20then%20it%20%E2%80%98may%20be%20highly%20useful%E2%80%99.%20However%2C%20on%20the%20second%20point%20he%20called%20the%20power%20of%20punishment%20exercised%20by%20the%20superintendent%20%E2%80%98a%20deformity%20in%20this%20government.%E2%80%99%20He%20chastised%20the%20police%20for%20having%20power%20outside%20the%20law%2C%20which%20in%20its%20nature%20was%20%E2%80%98dark%2C%20%5Band%5D%20unauthorized%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20other%20justices%20agreed%20that%20the%20superintendents%20had%20failed%20to%20act%20moderately%20but%20upheld%20the%20necessity%20of%20summary%20power%20to%20suit%20the%20purposes%20of%20justice.%20In%20Hyde%E2%80%99s%20words%2C%20%E2%80%98if%20all%20these%20offences%20were%20to%20be%20tried%20by%20English%20law%2C%20all%20the%20Englishmen%20in%20the%20settlement%20would%20be%20hardly%20sufficient%20for%20the%20purpose.%E2%80%99%20Chambers%20was%20more%20direct%20in%20advocating%20the%20need%20for%20summary%20punishment%3A%20%E2%80%98Every%20man%20who%20has%20been%20a%20long%20resident%20in%20this%20country%20would%20admit%20the%20expedience%2C%20if%20not%20the%20necessity%20of%20corporal%20punishment%20for%20such%20offences%20and%20I%20think%20the%20exercise%20of%20summary%20justice%20is%20essential%20to%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20British%20government%20here.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%2C%20of%20course%2C%20harboured%20the%20view%20that%20the%20situation%20of%20justice%20desired%20the%20superintendent%20to%20wield%20summary%20power%20even%20when%20the%20office%20of%20the%20superintendent%20itself%20was%20repetitively%20accepted%20to%20be%20illegal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20tussle%20between%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20expediency%20of%20summary%20justice%20was%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20creation%20of%20this%20office%20in%201772-73.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWarren%20Hastings%20reasoned%2C%20%E2%80%98A%20rigid%20observance%20of%20the%20letter%20of%20the%20law%20is%20a%20blessing%20in%20a%20well%20regulated%20state%2C%20but%20in%20a%20Government%20loose%20as%20that%20of%20Bengal%20is%2C%20and%20must%20be%20for%20some%20years%20to%20come%2C%20an%20extraordinary%20and%20exemplary%20coercion%20must%20be%20applied%20to%20eradicate%20those%20evils%20which%20the%20law%20cannot%20reach.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20summary%20mode%20of%20justice%20was%20thus%20justified%20precisely%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20will%20usher%20in%20a%20just%20system%2C%20security%2C%20and%20order.%20It%20was%20an%20accompaniment%20rather%20than%20the%20adversary%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20in%20these%20%E2%80%98some%20years%20to%20come%E2%80%99%2C%20William%20Jones%20constantly%20reproached%20the%20government%20for%20allowing%20police%20to%20exercise%20arbitrary%20power.%20In%20his%20address%20to%20the%20Grand%20Jury%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%201788%2C%20he%20said%20the%20superintendent%E2%80%99s%20powers%20are%20%E2%80%98dark%20and%20undefined%2C%20which%20our%20law%20most%20abhors%E2%80%99.%20The%20government%20nonetheless%20allowed%20the%20superintendents%20to%20exercise%20their%20arbitrary%20power%20and%20footed%20the%20bills%20of%20the%20fines%20which%20they%20received%2C%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20rectify%20the%20illegality%20of%20this%20office%2C%20an%20ordinance%20was%20brought%20in%201778.%20Interestingly%2C%20it%20was%20nullified%20by%20none%20other%20than%20the%20King-in-Council%20in%20London.%20It%20accused%20the%20Bengal%20government%20of%20creating%20%E2%80%98a%20dangerous%20power%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20position%20of%20the%20superintendent.%20A%20series%20of%20regulations%20were%20subsequently%20brought%20in%20to%20establish%20the%20body%20of%20commissioners%20of%20police.%20They%20were%20enshrined%20with%20the%20tasks%20of%20maintaining%20drainage%2C%20survey%20and%20repair%20roads%2C%20numbering%20the%20streets%2C%20keeping%20the%20city%20clean%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20However%2C%20the%20office%20of%20the%20superintendent%20continued%20to%20exist%20until%201793%20and%20it%20continued%20to%20use%20its%20arbitrary%20summary%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20would%20have%20expected%20that%20the%20practice%20of%20summary%20power%20would%20have%20ended%20with%20the%20abolition%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20superintendent%20and%20the%20subsequent%20appointment%20of%20police%20magistrates%20or%20justices%20of%20the%20peace%2C%20but%20it%20lingered%20on%2C%20and%20perhaps%20became%20worse.%20In%20a%20note%20written%20in%201814%2C%20the%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20laid%20out%20proper%20objectives%20of%20the%20police.%20First%2C%20it%20was%20meant%20to%20prevent%20crime%20and%2C%20second%2C%20to%20carry%20out%20inquiry%20after%20the%20crime%20was%20committed.%20The%20third%20was%20in%20apprehending%20the%20offender%20but%20any%20union%20of%20these%20powers%20with%20those%20of%20trial%20and%20punishment%2C%20he%20reasoned%2C%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98dangerous%20tendency%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20dangerous%20tendency%20did%20not%20fizzle%20out%20in%20the%20coming%20decades.%20The%20epitome%20was%20reached%20in%20the%201830s%20when%20the%20law%20commissioners%20who%20drafted%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20it%20is%20too%20common%20a%20practice%20for%20magistrates%20to%20decide%20what%20law%20is.%E2%80%9D%20If%20one%20reads%20the%20letters%20written%20by%20David%20McFarlan%2C%20who%20was%20the%20chief%20police%20magistrate%20in%20Calcutta%20in%20the%201830s%2C%20the%20words%20of%20the%20law%20commissioners%20would%20appear%20an%20understatement.%20The%20magistrates%20did%20not%20decide%20what%20the%20law%20was%2C%20but%20they%20were%20law%20unto%20themselves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20letter%20written%20to%20his%20father%20in%20England%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CYour%20heart%20grow%20grit%20to%20see%20the%20Lady%20Davy%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20crowd%20of%20Hindoos%20sitting%20upon%20his%20Arab%20horse%20examining%20into%20the%20merits%20of%20a%20boundary%20dispute%2C%20to%20see%20both%20parties%20respecting%20him%20for%20the%20pains%20he%20takes%20and%20the%20patience%20with%20which%20hears%20all%20they%20have%20to%20say%2C%20and%20in%20a%20case%20where%20one%20party%20has%20to%20suffer%20an%20injustice%20palpable%20only%20from%20actual%20inspection%2C%20to%20hear%20shouts%20of%20applause%20and%20blessings%20rise%20from%20a%20surrounding%20multitude%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20enough%20to%20turn%20a%20young%20head%20and%20certainly%20quite%20enough%20to%20make%20a%20papa%20as%20happy%20as%20a%20prince.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20his%20grandma%2C%20he%20boasted%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20decisions%20are%20relied%20on%20with%20as%20much%20confidence%20and%20carried%20out%20with%20effect%20as%20fully%20as%20those%20of%20the%20Lords%20of%20Council%20and%20Session.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPast%E2%80%99s%20presence%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20the%20arbitrary%20power%20of%20the%20police%20share%20an%20uneasy%20but%20proximate%20relationship.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECharles%20Playdell%20and%20Thomas%20Motte%20were%20heavily%20popular%20police%20superintendents%20in%20Calcutta%20in%20the%20late18th%20century.%20%E2%80%98Motte%E2%80%99s%20Cutcherry%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20the%20police%20court%20was%20called%20in%20the%201780s%2C%20was%20a%20popular%20reference%20point%20in%20the%20city.%20Summary%20justice%20had%20an%20appeal%20amongst%20elites%2C%20workers%2C%20shopkeepers%2C%20artisans%2C%20and%20other%20sorts%20of%20people.%20It%20flourished%20not%20in%20spite%20but%20because%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHindi%20proverbs%20celebrate%20the%20idea%20of%20litigation%20as%20the%20mechanism%20of%20true%20revenge.%20If%20one%20has%20to%20trouble%20their%20kin%20or%20neighbours%20for%20a%20long%2C%20long%20time%2C%20as%20the%20proverbs%20go%2C%20they%20should%20get%20them%20framed%20under%20the%20law.%20If%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20is%20touted%20as%20one%20stretching%20the%20process%20of%20justice%20to%20abnormally%20long%20periods%2C%20then%20the%20rule%20of%20police%20is%20regarded%20as%20speedy%20and%20instant.%20Police%20usually%20sides%20with%20the%20powerful%20but%20visits%20to%20the%20court%20are%20still%20to%20be%20avoided%20as%20far%20as%20possible.%20In%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20every%20section%20of%20the%20society%20would%20ideally%20prefer%20to%20use%20the%20coercive%20and%20summary%20power%20of%20the%20police%20for%20their%20benefit%20but%20at%20the%20larger%20level%20both%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20rule%20of%20police%20tend%20to%20stabilise%20the%20existing%20social%20order.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorically%2C%20when%20it%20came%20to%20disciplining%20the%20labouring%20pool%2C%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20deliberately%20left%20that%20task%20to%20be%20performed%20by%20the%20arbitrary%20power%20of%20summary%20justice.%20The%20institution%20of%20the%20police%20was%20the%20political%20response%20of%20the%20colonial%20government%20to%20meet%20the%20immediate%20situation%20of%20labour%20discipline%20and%20crime.%20It%20made%20justice%20popular%20and%20folded%20the%20power%20of%20the%20law%20into%20the%20everyday%20coercive%20practices%20of%20the%20police.%20Expedience%20became%20the%20defining%20factor%20of%20this%20mode%20of%20governance%20rather%20than%20the%20rule-based%20idea%20of%20justice.%20Efficiency%20triumphed%20over%20concerns%20for%20rights.%20Immediacy%20and%20swiftness%20which%20are%20the%20hallmarks%20of%20a%20summary%20mode%20of%20punishment%20made%20the%20idea%20of%20justice%20itself%20popular.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20jugaad-justice%20of%20contemporary%20India%20is%20also%20a%20political%20performance%20of%20justice.%20The%20symbolic%20presence%20of%20the%20likes%20of%20McFarlan%20still%20pervades%20the%20political%20and%20legal%20lives%20in%20India.%20There%20is%20nothing%20unchanging%20in%20the%20last%20two%20hundred%20years.%20I%20am%20not%20drawing%20a%20direct%20line%20from%20the%20past%20into%20the%20present.%20But%20what%20is%20startling%20is%20the%20uncanny%20presence%20of%20the%20past%20in%20the%20present%2C%20around%20the%20same%20issues%20of%20the%20troubled%20relationship%20between%20law%20and%20justice%20that%20once%20constituted%20a%20vital%20theme%20of%20debate%20among%20lawmakers%2C%20jurists%20and%20public%20intellectuals%20in%20the%2018th%20century.%20When%20the%20justice%20of%20bulldozer%2C%20apparently%20done%20under%20some%20formal%20conditions%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20and%20when%20lynching%2C%20as%20a%20form%20of%20public%20justice%2C%20done%20with%20impunity%20towards%20law%2C%20are%20creating%20a%20new%20normal%20of%20social%20and%20political%20life%2C%20the%20question%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20law%20and%20justice%20deserves%20another%20robust%20debate%20in%20our%20contemporary%20times%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ENitin%20Sinha%20is%20a%20h%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eistorian%20and%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ECentre%20for%20Modern%20Oriental%20Studies%2C%20Berlin.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711161053000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F11082632%2FImage6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-troubled-history-of-the-relationship-between-law-and-justice%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20a%20time%20when%20'bulldozer%20justice'%20and%20mob%20lynching%20are%20creating%20a%20new%20normal%20of%20social%20and%20political%20life%2C%20the%20question%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20law%20and%20justice%20deserves%20another%20robust%20debate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-troubled-history-of-the-relationship-between-law-and-justice%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'We%20don't%20live%2C%20we're%20just%20alive'%3A%20Afghan%20girls%20despair%20at%20Taliban%20school%20ban%22%2