rong%3E%20%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20campaigning%20in%20India%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20is%20officially%20underway%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20travelled%20to%20Bhutan%20on%20Friday%20(March%2022)%2C%20receiving%20its%20highest%20award%2C%20pledging%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%20for%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20five-year%20plan%20and%20gaining%20an%20endorsement%20from%20the%20Bhutanese%20king%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cbright%E2%80%9D%20future%20with%20%E2%80%9Chim%20at%20the%20helm%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20arrived%20in%20Bhutan%20on%20Friday%20morning%2C%20with%20his%20visit%20delayed%20by%20a%20day%20due%20to%20snowy%20weather%20in%20Paro%2C%20where%20the%20airport%20is%20located.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20technically%20no%20explicit%20restrictions%20on%20Indian%20prime%20ministers%20making%20overseas%20trips%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20are%20announced%20and%20when%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fmcc%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emodel%20code%20of%20conduct%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20in%20place.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20last%20time%20that%20an%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20had%20been%20abroad%20during%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fold.eci.gov.in%2Ffiles%2Ffile%2F1927-general-election-to-the-lok-sabha-2009-model-code-of-conduct-reg%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20period%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20in%202009%2C%20when%20Manmohan%20Singh%20visited%20the%20UK%20for%20the%20G-20%20summit%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmindia.gov.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F02%2Fformer-PM-Manmohan-Singh-Visit-02.02.2016.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMarch%2031%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%20May%202018%2C%20Modi%20visited%20Nepal%20to%20pray%20at%20the%20Pashupatinath%20temple%20on%20the%20day%20voters%20in%20Karnataka%20were%20electing%20their%20state%20assembly.%20The%20opposition%20Congress%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fcongress-accuses-pm-modi-to-influence-karnataka-voters-through-nepal-temple-visits%2Farticleshow%2F64136447.cms%5C%22%3Eaccused%20him%20of%20violating%20the%20model%20of%20conduct%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20influence%20votersbut%20nothing%20came%20of%20its%20complaint.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Thimphu%20also%20comes%20just%20after%20the%20Bhutanese%20premier%20was%20in%20India%20last%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20highlight%20of%20the%20visit%2C%20which%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20termed%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20milestone%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20the%20conferment%20of%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20civilian%20award%2C%20the%20Druk%20Gyalpo%2C%20to%20Modi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFive%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20had%20unusually%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fuae-zayed-medal-modi-election-mcc%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannounced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20it%20was%20conferring%20the%20%E2%80%98Order%20of%20Zayed%E2%80%99%20to%20Modi%20in%20April%202019%2C%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20campaigning%20for%20the%20Indian%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20collected%20the%20UAE%20award%20just%20a%20few%20months%20later%20in%20August%202019%20after%20winning%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20time%2C%20Modi%20waited%20for%20three%20years%20to%20travel%20to%20Bhutan%20to%20receive%20the%20award%20after%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20king%20announced%20it%20in%202021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20award%20was%20conferred%2C%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20king%20praised%20the%20Indian%20PM%2C%20going%20so%20far%20as%20saying%20that%20Modi%20would%20need%20to%20be%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Chelm%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbright%E2%80%9D%20Indian%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20comments%20were%20startling%20as%20they%20came%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20Indian%20election%20season%2C%20with%20the%20Modi%20government%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20strenuous%20campaigning%20to%20return%20to%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20him%20at%20the%20helm%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20future%20is%20bright.%20And%20as%20I%20said%20before%2C%20a%20successful%20India%20means%20a%20bright%20future%20for%20Bhutan%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20Bhutanese.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PMO%20was%20quick%20to%20publicise%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20praise%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D2016116%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPrime%2520Minister%2520Modi%2520is%2520the%2CTashichhodzong%252C%2520Thimphu%2520in%2520December%25202021.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissuing%20a%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20emphasised%20the%20apparent%20strides%20India%20had%20made%20under%20Modi%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20citation%20added%20that%20the%20award%20also%20honours%20India%E2%80%99s%20rise%20as%20a%20global%20power%20under%20his%20leadership%2C%20and%20celebrates%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20special%20bond%20with%20India.%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20has%20set%20India%20on%20the%20path%20of%20transformation%2C%20and%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20moral%20authority%20and%20global%20influence%20have%20grown.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20announced%20that%20New%20Delhi%20will%20double%20its%20allocation%20for%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20thirteenth%20five-year%20plan%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20one.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20would%20also%20like%20to%20announce%20to%20my%20brothers%20and%20sisters%20of%20Bhutan%20that%20the%20government%20of%20India%20will%20provide%20a%20support%20of%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%20in%20this%20direction%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2FSpeeches-Statements-hi.htm%3Fdtl%2F37737%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20said%20in%20Thimphu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20India%20and%20Bhutan%20signed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F37731%2FList_of_Outcomes__State_visit_of_Prime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_to_Bhutan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eseven%20agreements%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20covering%20areas%20of%20energy%2C%20trade%2C%20digital%20connectivity%2C%20space%20and%20agriculture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20also%20took%20place%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20expedited%20talks%20with%20China%20on%20resolving%20their%20boundary%20dispute.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnswering%20questions%20at%20a%20briefing%20in%20Thimpu%2C%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20Kwatra%20said%20that%20the%20Bhutan-China%20boundary%20discussions%20were%20%E2%80%9Cmatters%20between%20those%20two%20countries%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CInsofar%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20Bhutan%20are%20concerned%2C%20as%20today%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20state%20visit%20of%20the%20honourable%20prime%20minister%20very%20clearly%20signifies%2C%20they%20stand%20on%20their%20own%20footing%20and%20they%20are%20independent%20of%20relations%20with%20other%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKwatra%20also%20underlined%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccore%20fundamentals%E2%80%9D%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20Bhutan%20were%20%E2%80%9Ctrust%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csensitivity%20to%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20interests%20and%20concerns%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fbilateral-documents.htm%3Fdtl%2F37740%2FJoint_Statement_on_the_State_Visit_of_Prime_Minister_of_India_to_Bhutan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20joint%20statement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20issued%20after%20the%20formal%20talks%20stated%20that%20both%20sides%20%E2%80%9Cagree%20to%20continue%20with%20our%20close%20coordination%20and%20cooperation%20with%20each%20other%20on%20issues%20relating%20to%20our%20national%20interests%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20has%20been%20keenly%20following%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20boundary%20talks%20with%20China%20as%20some%20of%20the%20disputed%20areas%20are%20adjacent%20to%20the%20crucial%20Siliguri%20corridor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fbhutan-pm-india-vist-china-border-talks-shadow%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20reported%20last%20week%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20India%20had%20proposed%20to%20build%20a%20road%20through%20Bhutan%20to%20connect%20Tawang%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20to%20Guwahati%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20Bhutan%20had%20been%20hesitant%20due%20to%20concerns%20that%20this%20may%20complicate%20its%20ongoing%20boundary%20talks%20with%20China%20aimed%20at%20demarcating%20their%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeijing%20has%20been%20incrementally%20encroaching%20on%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20borders%2C%20a%20tactic%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fdiplomacy%2Farticle%2F3251394%2Fchinese-village-construction-disputed-zone-outpaces-china-bhutan-border-talks%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esalami%20slicing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20prompting%20Thimphu%E2%80%99s%20urgency%20in%20resolving%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711134096000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%