%2F3076973126_ab45efee1b_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Transparency%20activist%20Commodore%20(retd)%20Lokesh%20Batra%20has%20got%20RTI%20replies%20from%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20to%20his%20queries%20on%20the%20number%20of%20political%20parties%20that%20had%20opened%20current%20accounts%20for%20electoral%20bonds%20early%2C%20starting%20from%20March%2031%2C%202018%2C%20and%20also%20their%20eligibility%20for%20receiving%20the%20bonds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20SBI%20has%20told%20Batra%20that%20only%20three%20political%20parties%20had%20opened%20accounts%20for%20encashing%20electoral%20bonds%20until%20March%2031%2C%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20March%2031%2C%202019%2C%20the%20total%20number%20of%20parties%20that%20had%20opened%20accounts%20for%20encashing%20the%20bonds%20had%20increased%20to%2014%2C%20the%20bank%20told%20Batra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20little%20over%20a%20week%20later%2C%20on%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20the%20number%20of%20political%20parties%20that%20had%20opened%20accounts%20had%20gone%20up%20to%2018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20March%2031%2C%202020%2C%20there%20were%2022%20parties%20with%20accounts%20for%20and%20that%20were%20eligible%20to%20receive%20electoral%20bonds.%20This%20number%20remained%20the%20same%20till%20March%2031%2C%202021.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20went%20up%20to%2024%20as%20of%20March%2031%2C%202022%20and%20further%20to%2025%20as%20of%20March%2031%2C%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20of%20March%2021%2C%202024%2C%20the%20number%20remained%20the%20same%20at%2025%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20SBI%20has%20not%20identified%20the%20parties%20concerned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F716061466%2FSBI-D-TB-Responses-Dated-22-03-2024-on-02-Sepa