antej%2Cwell%252C%2520is%2520meant%2520for%2520Dalits.%5C%22%3E%20extreme%20precarity%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20vulnerability%20to%20sexual%20abuse%20by%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20becomes%20more%20alarming%20because%20groundwater%20levels%20in%20South%20Asia%20are%20heavily%20impacted%20by%20salinity%20in%20coastal%20areas.%20Gujarat%20has%20the%20longest%20coastline%20in%20India%20and%20water%20from%20wells%20is%20already%20undrinkable%20like%20some%20villages%20in%20Jafrabad%20district%20where%20women%20are%20forced%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahmedabadmirror.com%2Fat-this-amreli-village-water-pips-jingoism-as-poll-issue%2F68928865.html%5C%22%3Ewalk%20miles%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20access%20safe%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20inflicts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahmedabadmirror.com%2Fat-this-amreli-village-water-pips-jingoism-as-poll-issue%2F68928865.html%5C%22%3Edisproportionate%20burdens%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20marginalised%20groups.%20Discriminatory%20practices%20in%20access%20to%20water%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fservices%2Faop-cambridge-core%2Fcontent%2Fview%2F944A18883970B826970525435AA4A837%2Fstamped-9781009171915c9_p183-206_CBO.pdf%2Fintersectional_water_justice_in_india_at_the_confluence_of_gender_caste_and_climate_change.pdf%5C%22%3E%20continue%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20concerns%20of%20caste%20pollution%20%E2%80%93%20a%20belief%20among%20the%20upper%20castes%20that%20their%20%E2%80%98purity%E2%80%99%20will%20be%20defiled%20if%20they%20come%20into%20contact%20with%20lower-caste%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEfforts%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fservices%2Faop-cambridge-core%2Fcontent%2Fview%2F944A18883970B826970525435AA4A837%2Fstamped-9781009171915c9_p183-206_CBO.pdf%2Fintersectional_water_justice_in_india_at_the_confluence_of_gender_caste_and_climate_change.pdf%5C%22%3E%20decentralise%3C%2Fa%3E%20water%20governance%20in%20Gujarat%20continue%20to%20meet%20resistance%20from%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20people%20for%20whom%20equity%20of%20access%20disrupts%20their%20monopoly%20over%20irrigation%20and%20agricultural%20uses.%20Maintaining%20control%20of%20water%20access%20gives%20upper%20castes%20an%20advantage%20over%20lower-caste%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20injustices%20remain%20marginal%20considerations%20for%20intervention%20by%20NGOs%20and%20state%20governments.%20The%20problem%20of%20access%20to%20public%20resources%20based%20on%20social%20difference%20thus%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20urgently%20by%20policy-makers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernments%20have%20failed%20to%20acknowledge%20social%20discrimination%20in%20the%20provision%20of%20basic%20amenities%20to%20marginalised%20communities%20which%20will%20grow%20increasingly%20vulnerable%20as%20climate%20change%20intensifies%20long-standing%20social%20disparities%20in%20wealth%20and%20resource%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImproving%20public%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fengage%2Farticle%2Fwho-will-guard-guardians-state-accountability%5C%22%3Eaccountability%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20governance%20requires%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20numerous%20disadvantages%20faced%20by%20marginalised%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20India%E2%80%99s%20summer%20approaching%20and%20water%20stress%20becoming%20a%20reality%2C%20poor%20and%20marginalised%20women%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewhumanitarian.org%2Fnews-feature%2F2023%2F07%2F20%2Fits-all-our-burden-poorest-women-hardest-hit-heatwaves-india%5C%22%3Ebear%20the%20brunt%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20heat%20stress%20in%20the%20collection%20of%20water%2C%20a%20fact%20unrecognised%20by%20policymakers%20and%20insufficiently%20addressed%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fclimate%2Findia-heat-action-plans-overlook-the-vulnerable%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520country%26amp%3Bapos%3Bs%2520first%2520Heat%2520Action%2Cas%2520moves%2520targeted%2520at%2520poor%5C%22%3EHeat%20Action%20Plans%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWater%20scarcity%20and%20water%20insecurity%20are%20created%20through%20socio-economic%20and%20political%20inequalities.%20Socially%20just%20climate%20adaptation%20for%20water%20management%20can%20go%20hand-in-hand%20with%20an%20acknowledgement%20of%20the%20social%20power%20vested%20in%20local%20elites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerating%20institutional%20change%20from%20both%20above%20and%20below%20requires%20addressing%20the%20various%20barriers%20that%20prevent%20achieving%20human%20rights%20for%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20communities.%20It%20also%20demands%20political%20mobilisation%20towards%20overcoming%20social%20barriers%20in%20the%20same%20vein%20as%20the%20Mahad%20Satyagraha%20of%201927.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiving%20everyone%20a%20say%20in%20decision-making%20and%20removing%20unequal%20administrative%20measures%20that%20prevent%20fair%20access%20to%20water%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20making%20tubewells%20a%20public%20good%20with%20parameters%20of%20equal%20access%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20pursued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegal%20provisions%20towards%20supporting%20water%20equality%20need%20to%20be%20made%20enforceable.%20Otherwise%20the%20idea%20of%20water%20justice%20remains%20a%20mere%20tokenism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EPrakash%20Kashwan%20is%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholarworks.brandeis.edu%2Fesploro%2Fprofile%2Fprakash_kashwan%2Foverview%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EAssociate%20Professor%20of%20Environmental%20Studies%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20and%20Chair%2C%20Environmental%20Justice%20Concentration%2C%20MPP%2C%20at%20the%20Heller%20School%20for%20Social%20Policy%20%26amp%3B%20Management%20at%20Brandeis%20University.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20Democracy%20in%20the%20Woods%3A%20Environmental%20Conservation%20and%20Social%20Justice%20in%20India%2C%20Tanzania%2C%20and%20Mexico%20(Oxford%20University%20Press%2C%202017)%20and%20the%20Editor%20of%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Fclimate-justice-in-india%2F9728CA91D37ABECD4816C16BA3198873%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EClimate%20Justice%20in%20India%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20(Cambridge%20University%20Press%2C%202022).%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20by%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711115151000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19165415%2Fimage-1409.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Faccess-to-water-is-a-crisis-for-the-powerless%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fair%20access%20to%20water%20is%20an%20issue%20for%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20India.%20Who%20controls%20access%20and%20how%20this%20is%20governed%20needs%20fixing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Faccess-to-water-is-a-crisis-for-the-powerless%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222020%20Delhi%20Riots%3A%20Those%20Facing%20Graver%20Allegations%20Granted%20Bail%2C%20Says%20Umar%20Khalid%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F18112637%2FUmar-Khalid.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20the%202020%20Northeast%20Delhi%20riots%20%E2%80%98larger%20conspiracy%20case%E2%80%99%2C%20arguing%20for%20bail%2C%20Umar%20Khalid%20said%20that%20others%20with%20graver%20allegations%20were%20out%20on%20bail%20and%20some%20allegedly%20involved%20in%20similar%20activities%20weren%E2%80%99t%20accused%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fdelhi%2Fdelhi-riots-larger-conspiracy-case-granted-bail-umar-khalid-9226972%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhalid%20faced%20charges%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20he%20withdrew%20his%20bail%20plea%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20His%20lawyer%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20cited%20a%20%E2%80%9Cchange%20in%20circumstances%E2%80%9D%20and%20planned%20to%20pursue%20bail%20in%20the%20trial%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20try%20our%20luck%20in%20the%20trial%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%20(March%2021)%2C%20advocate%20Trideep%20Pais%2C%20appearing%20for%20Khalid%2C%20revealed%20the%20change%20of%20circumstances%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Karkardooma%20Court%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20factual%20basis%20on%20which%20three%20accused%20in%20the%20case%20have%20been%20granted%20bail%20have%20several%20overlaps%20with%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20court%20could%20consider%20if%20Khalid%20was%20entitled%20to%20a%20bail%20of%20parity%20even%20though%20he%20was%20charged%20with%20the%20stringent%20UAPA%20as%20the%20law%20was%20interpreted%20differently%20by%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20in%202023%2C%20the%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20must%20be%20satisfied%20with%20the%20probative%20value%20of%20evidence%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20examining%20bail%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais%2C%20adding%20that%20no%20terrorist%20act%20had%20been%20attributed%20to%20the%20accused%20by%20the%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20change%20of%20circumstances%20cited%20by%20the%20advocate%20was%20the%20continued%20incarceration%20of%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20cited%20Pais%20as%20saying%20that%20the%20prosecution%20cited%2015%20instances%20to%20point%20out%20the%20involvement%20of%20the%20accused%20%E2%80%93%20in%20many%20of%20these%2C%20there%20were%20no%20witnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20said%20the%20prosecution%20also%20mentioned%20four%20WhatsApp%20groups%20in%20the%20chargesheet%20to%20allege%20a%20conspiracy%20%E2%80%93%20out%20of%20these%2C%20he%20said%20Khalid%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20part%20of%20two%20groups.%20He%20alleged%20that%20many%20persons%20in%20these%20two%20groups%20were%20not%20even%20made%20an%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20one%20group%2C%20Khalid%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20send%20a%20single%20message.%20In%20the%20fourth%20WhatsApp%20group%20which%20Khalid%20was%20a%20part%20of%2C%20he%20sent%20only%20five%20messages%20%E2%80%93%20three%20of%20which%20were%20Google%20Maps%20locations%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20daily%20quoted%20Pais%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhalid%20also%20put%20up%20a%20message%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20police%20to%20call%20off%20the%20protest%2C%20claimed%20Pais.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20accused%20never%20instigated%20violence%20through%20this%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20two%20accused%20who%20were%20in%20Northeast%20Delhi%20during%20the%20riots%20are%20on%20bail.%20They%E2%80%99re%20in%20the%20same%20group%20as%20me%E2%80%A6%20they%E2%80%99re%20far%20more%20involved%20in%20the%20group%E2%80%A6%20a%20witness%20also%20made%20a%20direct%20allegation%20of%20rioting%20against%20these%20two%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20just%20two%20of%20the%20seven%20persons%20being%20made%20an%20accused%3F%20What%20makes%20them%20stand%20out%3F%E2%80%9D%20said%20Pais%2C%20adding%20that%20participation%20in%20a%20meeting%20whose%20contents%20were%20unknown%20to%20the%20prosecution%20was%20not%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20cited%20an%20instance%20where%20there%20was%20a%20witness%2C%20noting%20that%20his%20statements%2C%20when%20compared%20with%20the%20chargesheet%2C%20were%20incorrect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20granted%20bail%20to%20co-accused%20Asif%20Iqbal%20Tanha%20despite%20the%20same%20witness%20attributing%20more%20severe%20crimes%20to%20Tanha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Pais%20mentioned%20another%20instance%20where%20the%20prosecution%20alleged%20that%20three%20accused%20had%20conspired%20in%20Shaheen%20Bagh%2C%20but%20argued%20that%20the%20accused%20were%20not%20visible%20in%20any%20CCTV%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPais%20also%20argued%20that%20in%20other%20instances%20of%20meetings%20with%20other%20co-accused%2C%20their%20CDRs%20didn%E2%80%99t%20match%20with%20Khalid%E2%80%99s.%20%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99re%20all%20at%20different%20locations%E2%80%A6%20how%20did%20they%20plan%20a%20grand%20conspiracy%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20time%20India%20announced%20that%20(then%20US%20President%20Donald)%20Trump%20would%20visit%20(was)%20on%20January%2013.%20The%20prosecution%20claims%20that%20the%20accused%20gathered%20on%20January%208%20to%20disrupt%20his%20event%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20nobody%20even%20knew%20that%20Trump%20was%20coming%20to%20India%20on%20January%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20Khalid%2C%20the%20other%20individuals%20accused%20in%20the%20case%20are%20Devangana%20Kalita%2C%20Natasha%20Narwal%2C%20Asif%20Iqbal%20Tanha%2C%20former%20AAP%20councillor%20Tahir%20Hussain%2C%20Khalid%20Saifi%2C%20ex-Congress%20councillor%20Ishrat%20Jahan%2C%20Safoora%20Zargar%2C%20Sharjeel%20Imam%2C%20Meeran%20Haider%2C%20Gulfisha%20Fatima%2C%20Shifa-Ur-Rehman%2C%20Shadab%20Ahmed%2C%20Tasleem%20Ahmed%2C%20Saleem%20Malik%2C%20Mohd.%20Saleem%20Khan%2C%20Athar%20Khan%2C%20and%20Faizal%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Tanha%2C%20Narwal%2C%20and%20Kalita%20have%20been%20released%20on%20bail%2C%20the%20remaining%2014%20accused%20have%20been%20incarcerated%20for%20the%20past%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpolice-witness-not-credible-callous-probe-how-the-delhi-riots-cases-have-evolved%5C%22%3Ehad%20earlier%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20judges%20rapped%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20for%20%E2%80%98biased%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98improper%E2%80%99%20investigation%20into%20the%20Delhi%20riots.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20courts%20have%20rapped%20the%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20which%20comes%20under%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FDelhi%2F2020-delhi-riots-fabricated-evidence-hostile-witness-and-a-case-of-shoddy-probe%2Farticle66955373.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98fabrication%20of%20evidence%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FDelhi%2F2020-delhi-riots-fabricated-evidence-hostile-witness-and-a-case-of-shoddy-probe%2Farticle66955373.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98shoddy%20probe%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-police-northeast-riots-investigation%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%98a%20lack%20of%20logic%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711114240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F18112637%2FUmar-Khalid.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F2020-delhi-riots-those-facing-graver-allegations-granted-bail-says-umar-khalid%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20February%2C%20Khalid%20withdrew%20his%20bail%20plea%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20His%20lawyer%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20cited%20a%20%26quot%3Bchange%20in%20circumstances%26quot%3B%20and%20planned%20to%20pursue%20bail%20in%20the%20trial%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F2020-delhi-riots-those-facing-graver-allegations-granted-bail-says-umar-khalid%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22