tal%20substance%E2%80%99%20for%20human%20existence%20but%20is%20also%20a%20%E2%80%98peace%20keeper%E2%80%99.%20Acknowledging%20the%20collective%20action%20on%20conserving%20water%2C%20reflecting%20on%20community-based%20practices%20of%20water%20management%20can%20help%20us%20locate%20the%20role%20of%20water%20in%20bringing%20peace%20to%20individuals%2C%20communities%20and%20humanity.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorically%20speaking%2C%20shortage%20of%20water%20has%20brought%20distress%2C%20migration%20and%20violence.%20Societies%20that%20manage%20their%20water%20judiciously%20have%20largely%20been%20peaceful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPeace%20for%20individuals%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20present%2C%20the%20most%20crucial%20issue%20that%20lies%20before%20us%20is%20that%20of%20global%20climate%20change.%20Increasing%20number%20of%20people%20are%20now%20turning%20into%20%E2%80%98climate%20refugees%E2%80%99%20i.e.%20individuals%20who%20are%20forced%20to%20leave%20their%20country%20due%20to%20short-term%20or%20long-term%20climate%20crises%20like%20drought%2C%20flood%2C%20deforestation%20etc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20These%20individuals%20live%20a%20distressed%20and%20undignified%20life%2C%20bordered%20nation-states%20inflict%20violence%20on%20them%2C%20considering%20them%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20domestic%20population.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20High%20Commissioner%20for%20Refugees%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EUNHCR)%2C%20%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unhcr.org%2Fin%2Fnews%2Fstories%2Ffrequently-asked-questions-climate-change-and-disaster-displacement%5C%22%3E21.5%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20an%20average%20are%20forcibly%20displaced%20each%20year%20because%20of%20climate-related%20problems.%20An%20internationally%20acclaimed%20think%20tank%2C%20Institute%20for%20Economics%20and%20Peace%20(IEP)%2C%20predicts%20that%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economicsandpeace.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2FEcological-Threat-Register-Press-Release-27.08-FINAL.pdf%5C%22%3E%201.2%20billion%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20dislocated%20globally%20by%202050%20due%20to%20environmental%20change%2C%20conflict%20and%20civil%20unrest.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20conservation%20and%20management%20of%20limited%20water%20resources%20would%20guarantee%20peace%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20people%20and%20ensure%20that%20they%20attain%20a%20dignified%20livelihood%20in%20their%20own%20country%20or%20region.%20For%20instance%2C%20due%20to%20water%20scarcity%20in%20Dholpur%20and%20Karauli%20districts%20in%20Rajasthan%20many%20local%20residents%20led%20a%20life%20of%20desperation%20and%20even%20migrated%20to%20work%20as%20labourers%20which%20resulted%20in%20family%20fragmentation%20etc.%20Moreover%2C%20some%20people%20in%20these%20areas%20even%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eresorted%20to%20illegal%20occupation%20like%20dacoity.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20efforts%20of%20NGOs%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ETarun%20Bharat%20Sangh%20spanning%20over%20decades%2C%20dead%20perennial%20rivers%20%E2%80%94%20Sairni%20and%20Parvati%20%E2%80%94%20were%20rejuvenated%20in%20this%20region.%20So%2C%20when%20the%20area%20started%20getting%20water%2C%20the%20gun%20toting%20men%20turned%20to%20agriculture.%20This%20is%20how%20water%20brought%20peace%20to%20individuals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPeace%20for%20community%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnly%20peaceful%20individuals%20can%20create%20and%20sustain%20peaceful%20communities.%20Water%20is%20essential%20to%20bring%20peace%20within%20and%20among%20communities.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20also%20true%20that%20community%20efforts%20are%20more%20important%20than%20individuals%20to%20effectively%20conserve%20water%20resources.%20There%20is%20a%20growing%20acknowledgement%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20community%20practices%20of%20water%20management.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20United%20Nations%20Educational%2C%20Scientific%20and%20Cultural%20Organisation%20(UNESCO)%20chair%20in%20community-based%20research%20and%20social%20responsibility%20in%20higher%20education%20released%20a%20book%20titled%2C%20%3Cem%3EBridging%20Knowledge%20Cultures%3A%20Rebalancing%20power%20in%20the%20co-construction%20of%20Knowledge%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0edited%20by%20Walter%20Lepore%2C%20Budd%20L.%20Hall%20and%20Rajesh%20Tandon.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20book%20talks%20about%20ten%20authentic%20case%20studies%20of%20community%20knowledge%20cultures.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fcaste-water-access-missing-india-environmental-discourse%5C%22%3ECaste%E2%80%99s%20Role%20in%20Shaping%20Water%20Access%20Is%20Missing%20From%20Indian%20Environmental%20Discourse%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETarun%20Bharat%20Sangh%20has%20itself%20published%20two%20books%20%3Cem%3ERejuvenation%20of%20rivers%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0published%20in%202022%20and%20%3Cem%3EDecentralised%20and%20equitable%20climate%20resilience%20through%20community%20knowledge%2C%20rainwater%20capture%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20in%202023%20highlights%20how%20the%20local%20community%20knowledge%20of%20rainwater%20harvesting%2C%20constructing%20and%20maintaining%20traditional%20water%20bodies%20like%3Cem%3E%20johads%2C%20nadas%2C%20nadis%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20reviving%20dead%20perennial%20rivers%20like%20Agrani%2C%20Maharani%2C%20Sherni%2C%20etc.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20authors%20of%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC)%20synthesis%20reports%20might%2C%20however%2C%20not%20consider%20the%20narratives%20of%20communities%20as%20authentic%20sources%20of%20information.%20They%20rather%20rely%20on%20academically%20sanctioned%20%E2%80%98peer-reviewed%E2%80%99%20articles.%20The%20climate%2Fenvironmental%20scientists%20who%20dominate%20the%20domain%20of%20global%20climate%20policy%20fail%20to%20understand%20the%20essence%20of%20community%20knowledge%20culture%20as%20they%20lack%20the%20framework%20to%20do%20so.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20different%20UN%20bodies%20have%20completely%20different%20outlook%20towards%20community%20knowledge.%20To%20bring%20peace%20in%20the%20community%20through%20water%2C%20we%20need%20an%20alternative%20theoretical%20and%20methodological%20framework%20to%20understand%20and%20respect%20community%20knowledge%20cultures%20of%20water%20conservation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPeace%20for%20humanity%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Rajendra%20Singh%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20Waterman%20of%20India%2C%20highlighted%20that%20constructive%20and%20collective%20action%20to%20conserve%20and%20manage%20water%20will%20only%20be%20possible%20when%20we%20challenge%20the%20modern%20science%20that%20favours%20command%20and%20control%20technology%20and%20anthropocentric%20misuse%20of%20water%20commons.%20He%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%98science%20without%20sense%E2%80%99%20that%20has%20overdrafted%2062%25%20of%20underground%20aquifers%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20People%E2%80%99s%20science%20or%20people%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%20is%20epistemologically%20contradictory%20to%20modern%20science%2C%20it%20has%20an%20outlook%20of%20respect%20and%20nourishment%20towards%20commons%20unlike%20the%20one%20of%20control%20and%20exploitation%20held%20by%20the%20latter.%20Our%20imagination%20of%20development%20is%20appropriated%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98universal%20path%20of%20modern%20development%20backed%20by%20western%20science%E2%80%99%2C%20cognitive%20peace%20would%20come%20if%20we%20look%20at%20the%20pluriverse%20of%20knowledge(s)%20to%20govern%20commons%20that%20are%20already-existing%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Global%20South.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20philosophies%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20like%20Swaraj%20(Asia)%2C%20Buen%20Vivir%20(South%20America)%2C%20Ubuntu%20(Africa)%20etc.%20offer%20alternative%20sustainable%20pathways%20to%20manage%20commons%20and%20help%20us%20gain%20cognitive%20peace%2C%20the%20most%20essential%20one%20for%20humanity.%20Any%20efforts%2C%20individual%20or%20communal%2C%20modern%20or%20traditional%2C%20global%20or%20local%20would%20likely%20fail%20until%20we%20free%20ourselves%20%E2%80%98cognitively%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98growth%20monster%E2%80%99%20within%20ourselves.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20really%20need%20%E2%80%98Swaraj%20in%20ideas%E2%80%99%20to%20think%20beyond%20the%20modern%20hydraulic%20approach%20of%20water%20management.%20We%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20alternative%20pathways%20for%20water%20management%20especially%20the%20the%20Global%20South%20for%20peaceful%20co-existence.%20The%20frameworks%20of%20community%20knowledge%20have%20to%20be%20epistemically%20imbibed%20to%20claim%20that%20water%20can%20bring%20peace%20for%20the%20entire%20humanity.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20internalise%20the%20theme%20of%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20World%20Water%20Day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EPuneet%20Kumar%20is%20a%20doctoral%20candidate%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20University%20of%20Delhi.%20He%20works%20on%20politics%20of%20knowledge%20around%20urban%20water%20bodies%20in%20Delhi.%20He%20is%20a%20member%20of%20Yuva%20Jal%20Biradari%20and%20has%20also%20volunteered%20with%20Tarun%20Bharat%20Sangh%20to%20conserve%20traditional%20water%20bodies%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Haryana.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711112440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F22182534%2FScreenshot-