ling%20party%20leaders%20of%20encouraging%20lottery%20addiction.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Ftmc-anubrata-mondal-his-daughter-won-lottery-cbi-2296066-2022-11-11%5C%22%3EAnubrata%20Mandal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20jailed%20Birbhum%20district%20chief%20of%20TMC%2C%20had%20his%20family%20alone%20winning%20lotteries%20thrice%2C%20prompting%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20to%20probe%20Mandal%E2%80%99s%20lottery%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20main%20electoral%20funding%20came%20from%20a%20company%20headquartered%20outside%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20political%20funder%20favoured%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFour%20firms%2C%20part%20of%20the%20Kolkata-based%20M.K.%20Jalan%20group%20of%20companies%2C%20which%20include%20Keventers%2C%20have%20emerged%20as%20the%20third%20biggest%20political%20donor%20in%20the%20country%20with%20Rs%20616.9%20crore%20spending%2C%20next%20only%20to%20Future%20Gaming%20And%20Hotel%20Services%20and%20Telangana-based%20Megha%20Engineering%20(Rs%20966%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Jalans%20are%20followed%20by%20the%20Kolkata-based%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%2C%20the%20fourth-highest%20spender%20in%20the%20country%2C%20having%20donated%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20609%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchart-the-top-50-purchasers-of-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3EChart%3A%20The%20Top%2050%20Purchasers%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20by%20Promoter%2FGroup%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFunding%20pattern%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EData%20shows%20the%20two%20biggest%20political%20donors%20from%20Bengal%20%E2%80%93%20the%20M.K.%20Jalan%20group%20and%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%20%E2%80%93%20took%20distinctly%20different%20funding%20trajectories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EJalan%E2%80%99s%20funding%20overwhelmingly%20favoured%20the%20BJP%2C%20with%20Rs%20351.9%20crore%20or%2057%25%20of%20its%20donation%2C%20followed%20by%20Rs%20160.5%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%20and%20Rs%2084.4%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC.%20The%20largest%20portion%20was%20allocated%20to%20the%20BJP%20during%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGoenka%20heavily%20favoured%20the%20TMC%2C%20giving%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%2076%25%20of%20its%20total%20spending%20on%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20was%20another%20difference%20in%20their%20funding%20pattern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Jalans%E2%80%99%20largest%20expenditure%20incurred%20during%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20in%20April-May%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20the%20Rs%20390.5%20crore%2C%20the%20company%20gave%20Rs%20325%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20Rs%2031%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC%2C%20Rs%2024%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20Rs%2010%20crore%20to%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20and%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20to%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Goenkas%20gave%20Rs%2015%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20Rs%205%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC%20during%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20April%202021%2C%20during%20the%20state%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20company%20gave%20Rs%2041%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20Rs%2036%20crore%20to%20the%20TMC.%20However%2C%20after%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20return%20to%20power%2C%20funds%20flew%20into%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20accounts%20in%20rather%20large%20sums.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Jalan%20group%E2%80%99s%20funding%20to%20the%20Congress%20is%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENote%20that%20Congress%20leader%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20unit%20president%2C%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20had%20in%202018%20filed%20a%20case%20in%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court%20alleging%20irregularities%20in%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20Metro%20Dairy%20to%20the%20Jalan%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fchallenge-to-metro-dairy-selloff-spiked%2Fcid%2F1887104%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20alleged%20that%20there%20was%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20the%20Bengal%20government%E2%80%99s%20sale%20of%20its%2047%25%20stake%20in%20Metro%20Dairy%20to%20Keventer%20Agro%20Ltd%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20high%20court%20dismissed%20these%20allegations%2C%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-adhir-ranjan-chowdhury-metro-dairy-disinvestment-tmc-govt-209537%5C%22%3Eupheld%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20verdict%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20donors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOutside%20of%20these%20three%20firms%2C%20the%20TMC%20also%20got%20substantial%20donations%20from%20several%20other%20companies%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%2045.5%20crore%20from%20Avees%20Trading%20Finance%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20Rs%2042%20crore%20from%20IFB%20Agro%2C%20Rs%2040%20crore%20from%20Chennai%20Green%20Woods%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20and%20Rs%2038%20crore%20Prarambh%20Securities%20Pvt%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOther%20major%20donations%20to%20the%20TMC%20include%20Rs%2021%20crore%20from%20Transways%20Exim%20Private%20Limited%2C%20Rs%2018.5%20crore%20from%20Rashmi%20Cement%20Ltd%2C%20Rs.%2015.4%20crore%20from%20Westwell%20Gases%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20Rs.%2015%20crore%20from%20Misrilall%20Mines%2C%20Rs%2015%20crore%20from%20WPIL%20and%20Rs%2012.8%20crore%20from%20Himalayan%20Endeavour%20Pvt%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAmong%20them%2C%20Chennai%20Green%20Woods%20Pvt%20Ltd%20is%20based%20in%20Hyderabad%20and%20Prarambh%20Securities%20Pvt%20Ltd%20has%20its%20registered%20office%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20corporate%20office%20in%20Maharashtra.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20companies%20are%20headquartered%20in%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20these%20companies%2C%20Avees%20has%20also%20given%20Rs%2053%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20IFB%20gave%20Rs%2035%20crore%20to%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20Rashmi%20Cement%20gave%20Rs%2072%20crore%20to%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20and%20WPIL%20gave%20Rs%2015%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOther%20donors%20of%20the%20party%20include%20Sengupta%20And%20Sengupta%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs.%208.2%20crore)%2C%20Sandeep%20Auto%20Lines%20(7%20crore)%2C%20Tivoli%20Park%20Apartments%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(7%20crore)%2C%20Kamna%20Credits%20And%20Promoters%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(6%20crore)%2C%20Askus%20Logistics%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(5%20crore)%2C%20Asish%20Finance%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(5%20crore)%2C%20Herald%20Beverages%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%205.5%20crore)%2C%20ITC%20Ltd%20(Rs%204.9%20crore)%2C%20KVR%20Baseline%20Resources%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%204%20crore)%2C%20Kejriwal%20Miiniing%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%204%20crore)%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Waste%20Management%20Pvt%20Ltd%20(Rs%206%20crore)%20and%20Salasar%20Stock%20Broking%20Ltd-Proprietary%20(Rs%205%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20party%2C%20which%20has%20been%20ruling%20Bengal%20since%202011%2C%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20third-highest%20recipient%20of%20political%20donations%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%20Its%20earning%20of%20Rs%201%2C705%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20comes%20next%20only%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20Rajya%20Sabha%20members%20like%20Saket%20Gokhale%20and%20Jawhar%20Sircar%20have%20repeatedly%20used%20social%20media%20to%20target%20the%20BJP%20over%20alleged%20misuse%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme%2C%20none%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20senior%20leaders%20in%20West%20Bengal%20have%20commented%20in%20the%20past%20five%20weeks%20since%20the%20scrapping%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EReacting%20to%20the%20revelations%2C%20CPI(M)%20state%20secretary%20Md.%20Salim%20said%20last%20week%20that%20the%20data%20made%20it%20evident%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccorporates%20conspired%20against%20the%20Leftists%20to%20ensure%20there%20are%20no%20Left%20MPs%20from%20Bengal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20alleged%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccorporates%20funded%20the%20two%20pro-corporate%20parties%E2%80%9D%20to%20create%20a%20political%20binary%20around%20the%20TMC%20and%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%9Cso%20that%20they%20can%20loot%20and%20share%20the%20spoils%20in%20perfect%20understanding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20CPI(M)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthree-left-parties-declared-to-ec-that-they-dont-accept-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Edid%20not%20accept%20any%20donation%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20was%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme.%20The%20party%20has%20no%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20in%20the%20state%20since%202019%20and%20no%20MLA%20since%202021%2C%20as%20its%20vote%20share%20nosedived.%20Currently%2C%20the%20party%20is%20trying%20to%20highlight%20the%20massive%20corporate%20funding%20from%20Bengal%20corporates%20to%20these%20two%20parties%20to%20regain%20lost%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThey%20are%20set%20to%20contest%20the%20election%20in%20alliance%20with%20the%20Congress%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20even%20as%20the%20party%20will%20fight%20the%20Congress%20in%20Kerala%2C%20which%20the%20CPI(M)%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%